verbose_text: Indeed, SFN treatment that resulted in both cell cycle arrest and senescence (5 and 10 muM SFN, Fig. XREF_FIG) and apoptosis (20 muM SFN, Fig. XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY) also promoted autophagy in breast cancer cells that may be considered as both cytostatic autophagy (5 and 10 muM SFN) and cytotoxic autophagy (20 muM SFN).
